parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical grounding issue can cause the engine to quit suddenly without warning, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine quits suddenly
the speedometer stops working
ABS and check engine lights start flashing
the gear indicator flashes
the motorcycle is stuck in gear
the motor cuts in and out
turn signals and high beams indicator turn on
the horn does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ignition switch failure can cause the motorcycle to lose all power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The ignition switch fails
the motorcycle dies
all power is lost
the motor stops
the ignition switch turns back to the "on" position but nothing happens.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corroded ground spider can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The engine loses power
the speedometer and tachometer jump erratically
the bike restarts and regains power after a brief period.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil seal can cause oil to spill from the rear of the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents or engine damage.
symptoms: Oil spills from the rear of the vehicle
oil leak observed while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic shift system can cause the transmission to lock in a single gear, making it difficult or impossible to shift, which can lead to accidents or leave the rider stranded.
symptoms: The "Shift SH46" warning light appears on the dashboard
the transmission becomes stuck in a single gear (in this case
5th gear)
the paddle shifter and foot-operated manual shift are unresponsive
the engine stalls.
